UNITED STATES of America ex rel. Sylvester DOMALIK v. Byron GOODALL, Immigration Officer in Charge, and S. D. Smith District Director of Immigration of the United States Department of Labor. No. 4858. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Oct. 6, 1932. Oliver M. Loomis, U. S. Atty., and George L. Eulison, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of South Bend, Ind., for appellee.

Before ALSCIIULEE, EVANS, and SPAEKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellee, it is now here ordered and adjudged by this court that this cause he docketed in this court, and that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, pursuant to section 1 of rule 14 of the EuJes of this court.
